    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_004/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The research question and expected outputs focus on fingerprint-based spectral comparison, but the paper's primary workflow and examples demonstrate spectrum-to-spectrum comparison using spectral similarity measures (cosine, modified cosine), not molecular fingerprint-based comparison.",
        "Fingerprint functionality (rdkit-based morgan fingerprints with Dice/Jaccard/Cosine) is mentioned as a capability of matchms, but it appears to be a separate feature for comparing molecular fingerprints, not for comparing mass spectra via fingerprints.",
        "The example workflow in passage 4 uses Cosine similarity directly on spectra (not fingerprints), suggesting the primary use case differs from the card's focus."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
