      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/spectral-file-format-conversion/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Raw data can be imported from the commonly used formats msp, mzML (Martens et al., 2011), mzXML, MGF (mzML, mzXML, MGF file importers are built on top of pyteomics (Goloborodko, Levitsky, Ivanov, & Gorshkov, 2013; Levitsky, Klein, Ivanov, & Gorshkov, 2019), as well as from JSON files (as provided by GNPS), but also via Universal Spectrum Identifiers (USI) (Wang et al., 2020).",
      "asbval:note": "All formats mentioned in the claim are explicitly supported by matchms for import. The paper describes matchms as enabling processing and comparison workflows, supporting interoperability.",
